  <entry>
    <id>tag:www.gov.uk,2005:PublicationesquePresenter/61102</id>
    <published>2012-12-18T00:00:00+00:00</published>
    <updated>2012-12-21T11:59:20+00:00</updated>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/department-for-communities-and-local-government-approved-software-for-the-production-of-non-domestic-energy-performance-certificates-epc"/>
    <title>Department for Communities and Local Government approved software for the production of Non Domestic Energy Performance Certificates (EPC) </title>
    <category>Publication</category>
    <summary></summary>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Energy Performance of Buildings Directive (&lt;abbr title="Energy Performance of Buildings Directive"&gt;EPBD&lt;/abbr&gt;) became part of EU law in December 2002. The &lt;abbr title="Energy Performance of Buildings Directive"&gt;EPBD&lt;/abbr&gt; has been implemented into law via the &lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2007/991/contents/made"&gt;Energy Performance of Buildings (Certificates and Inspections) (England and Wales) Regulations 2007&lt;/a&gt; (S.I. 2007/991 as amended) (“the 2007 regulations”) in respect of sales and lettings, and in regulation 29 to 33 of the &lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2010/2214/contents/made"&gt;Building Regulations 2010&lt;/a&gt; (S.I. 2010/2214 as amended or superseded) (the Building Regulations) in respect of the duty on construction.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regulation 24 of the Building Regulations 2010 (the Building Regulations) requires the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government (the Secretary of State) to approve a National Calculation Methodology (&lt;abbr title="National Calculation Methodology"&gt;NCM&lt;/abbr&gt;) for calculating the energy performance of buildings.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All software that is used to assess the energy performance of buildings must be validated to ensure that it operates in a manner, and to a standard, consistent with the &lt;abbr title="National Calculation Methodology"&gt;NCM&lt;/abbr&gt; before it can be approved by the Secretary of State.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please see the attached latest list of approved software for the production of non domestic Energy Performance Certificates (EPCs), Domestic Energy Performance Certificates (DECs) and Air Conditioning Inspection Reports (ACIRs).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
